imgview - displays image files

   Forces startup in color-index mode. By default the color mode will
          be selected depending on the capabilities of the display server.

     When multiple images are specified on the command line they will be
     stacked with the first image on top.  Image views may be dragged around
     with left-mouse.  The image may be roamed inside a view with middle-
     mouse. Right-mouse will bring up a menu with various display options.  If
     an image is larger than the window, the center portion of the image will
     be displayed initially; the roam function can be used to navigate around
     the full image.
